    businessScene: "Basingstoke is a rare thing: a town with genuine corporate gravity. The AA and Sun Life Financial anchor the insurance and financial services sector from their HQs here, while Eli Lilly UK runs its British operations from the town. Sony Music Entertainment also has a significant presence. These large employers sustain a dense ecosystem of contractors, specialist suppliers, and professional services firms. The Town Centre and Chineham business parks host most of the tech and software activity, while logistics and engineering firms cluster around the A33 corridor and Brighton Hill. Hampshire Hospitals NHS adds a public-sector dimension, creating demand for payroll and VAT work from medical contractors. The local economy is distinctive for its mix of global HQs and homegrown SMEs, often spun out from those larger operations.",
