      body: "A small hospitality firm based near Tattenham Corner approached us. They operate a bar and event space that sees 60% of annual revenue during the Epsom Derby meeting. Their previous accountant had them on a standard VAT scheme, meaning they paid VAT monthly but could only reclaim on quarterly returns. We moved them to a monthly returns scheme aligned to their peak trading period, recovering \u00a314,720 in input VAT on refurbishment and stock purchased before Derby week. We also restructured their payroll to use zero-hours contracts with holiday pay accrued, reducing their employer NI liability by roughly \u00a32,400 a year. The owner, a former chef, now has a clear cashflow forecast for the off-season.",
