    businessScene: "Penzance's economy is anchored by tourism, fishing and maritime industries, alongside a significant public sector presence. The Isles of Scilly Steamship Company operates the passenger and freight link to the islands, supporting both tourism and local supply chains. Penlee Lifeboat (RNLI) and West Cornwall Hospital provide substantial employment, while Cornwall Council maintains a regional office presence. The Town Centre and Newlyn harbour area host a mix of retail, hospitality and fishing related businesses. Stein's Fish & Chips, a legacy employer, reflects the enduring importance of the seafood sector. Seasonal tourism drives demand for accommodation, food service and leisure businesses, while healthcare and public sector roles provide year round stability. The local economy is distinctive for its reliance on maritime infrastructure and the visitor economy, with many small businesses operating across both sectors.",
